## `Makefile`

```makefile
# File: Makefile

minigit: minigit.go
	go build -o minigit minigit.go

clean:
	rm -f minigit
	rm -rf .minigit
```

---

## How to Build & Run

1. Place the Go code above into a file called `minigit.go`.
2. Copy the `Makefile` into the same directory.
3. Run `make` to build, resulting in an executable named `minigit`.
4. Run tests as instructed:  
   ```sh
   bash test-v1.sh
   ```

---

**This implementation should handle the basic workflow and pass standard SPEC-style tests as referenced. If you have a stricter or different SPEC, or run into issues, please paste the actual SPEC provided and any test errors so I can further refine the implementation.**

